<H1 align=center>Computer Organization, CS-341</H1>
<H2 align=center>Dr. C. Vickery</H2>

Computer Science 341 is a required course for undergraduate majors
who have matriculated in either the BA or BS program. It is an
introduction to the design of a computer's hardware, particularly
the CPU and memory systems.

<H2>Course Topics</H2>

<UL>
  <LI>Quantifying Performance
  <LI>Encoding Information
  <LI>Combinational Logic
  <LI>Sequential Logic
  <LI>Programmable Logic
  <LI>Memory System Design and Control
  <LI>ALU Design and Control
  <LI>Data Path Design and Control
</UL>

<H2>Required Textbook</H2>
Tanenbaum, Andrew S.<BR>
<I>Computer Organization, Fourth Edition.</I><BR>
Prentice Hall, 1999. ISBN 0-13-095990-1.<P>

